Even if the court is satisfied that the local forum is not “clearly inappropriate”, the principle governing the issue of an “anti-suit” injunction depends upon the court being affirmatively satisfied that the foreign proceedings are vexatious or oppressive. Consequently, the mere failure of an application to stay the local proceedings (in accordance with the “clearly inappropriate forum” principles discussed in 
[s 67.55]
) does not establish that the local plaintiff is entitled to restrain the conduct of the foreign proceedings: Société Nationale Industrielle Aerospatiale v Lee Kui Jak [1987] AC 871; [1987] 3 All ER 510; [1987] 3 WLR 59 . This is because the domestic and foreign courts may both be appropriate fora for the proceedings.

